sentences: Dick Mine was born Tokuichi Mine (三根 徳一, Mine Tokuichi) on October 8, 1908, in the city of Tokushima.
On August 7, 1934, the band cut their first record.
In 1941, under pressure from anti-Western Japanese censors, Mine reverted to using Kōichi Mine as a stage name.
In the 1960s he became a prominent anti-nuclear activist.
In 1982, he enjoyed his last hit—a duet with Noriko Awaya called Modern Age.
Mine died from heart failure on June 10, 1991.
